      About this item

      • Remove Dead Skin Easily: This baby feet foot peel starts to exfoliate dead skin in just 12 days, results lasting up to 23 weeks. Perfect for dry feet treatment, callus remover and cracked heels.
      • Deep Hydration and Repair: Infused with Collagen, Argan Oil, Aloe Vera, and Vitamins A, C, and E, our foot mask for dry cracked feet deeply moisturizes, leaving your feet smooth and hydrated.
      • Gentle & Safe Peeling: Dermatologically tested, this feet exfoliator mask gently peels dead skin without irritation, making it the perfect foot care product for men and women.
      • Certified Quality & Safety: Our foot exfoliator is dermatologically tested and holds MSDS, GMP, and ISO certificates, guaranteeing safe and effective foot care you can trust.
      • Note: For best results, please follow the instructions carefully (refer to the product description). The feet peeling mask is suitable for normal and dry skin types.

      • I have very dry skin on my feet. Will this mask deal with this problem?

        This is a special foot mask with skin smoothing and moisturizing ingredients to get rid of coarse, dull, and dead skin on the feet. It is especially effective for the areas around the heel and foot.

      • Does the mask have a strong smell?

        The foot peel mask doesnt have any sharp or unpleasant smells, but it has a special own flavor because of its presence of active ingredients.

      • Is this product durable? What is the active ingredient, and how long will the effects last?

        Natural botanical extracts and foot-centric nutrients gently penetrate the old skin layers, breaking down rough, coarse dead skin safely and painlessly. This process nourishes and protects your newly exfoliated feet for an extended period.

      • Is the process of the extracts penetrating into the dead skin painful?

        No, our foot peel mask painlessly peels away dead cells and then nourishes and moisturizes foot skin to silky-softness.

      • Could you please provide the full list of Foot Peel Mask ingredients?

        Hello dear Customer! Here is the full list of ingredients: Water, Alcohol, Glycerol, Lactic Acid, Malic Acid, Aloe Vera extract, Sorbitol, Butylene Glycol, Papain, Citric Acid, Salicylic Acid, Collagen, Argan Oil, Vitamin A, Vitamin E.

      Important information

      Safety Information

      Do not use this product if you are a pregnant or nursing mother; If you are diabetic (consult your physician); If you are allergic to any of the ingredients in this product (see bottom of package), if you have open sores on your feet or other foot damage, or if you are using any other foot products. Before use, read the directions and follow them carefully. The product should be used immediately after opening plastic booties. Each Sunatoria Foot Mask is a single-use application. Do not re-use plastic booties. Sunatoria recommends staying seated during treatment for your safety. Keep the gel away from your eyes. If you experience any itching, redness, swelling, irritation, or inflammation, wash your feet and see a doctor. If the skin on your feet becomes too dry after using the product, a small amount of moisturizer can be applied. Do not forcibly remove the dead skin from your feet. Let the skin peel naturally. Storage: Keep out of reach of children at all times. Do not expose the product to extremely high or low temperatures and avoid exposure to direct sunlight. Do not use this product after the expiration date.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      • JK
        4.0 out of 5 stars Mostly Works
        Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2021
        Color: Aloe VeraVerified Purchase
        June 2021 for 7 Days.

        Caveats: To try this, I did nothing but wash my feet, soak them the first 4 days at 10 minutes each day, and did not use lotion or oils on my feet. I did go in a pool on Day 4. I am a diabetic, so I normally have diabetes-induced slightly dry skin.

        Night 1:
        Thoroughly washed and dried feet. Washed hands immediately after. Mask on with knee high socks over mask for 60 minutes.

        TIP: Use socks taller than ankle high. Mask covers ankles and can stick out of top leaking mask contents onto nearby surfaces. Changed to knee high socks.

        Removed mask. Washed and dried feet. Skin on feet felt oversaturated like when in a bath for too long. Once dry, the tops of toenails feel as if acetone has been on them too long, dried out.

        Day 2:
        Feet felt slightly dry. At night, soaked in cold water (it's summer during a heat wave). Dried feet. Skin felt "tight", along with a "tight/pulling" sensation around heels and top part of ankles, while rotating ankle muscles. Feel extremely dry. When wiggling toes, toes feel extremely dry.

        Day 3:
        Skin felt dry. Didn't feel the "tightness" as much as the previous day. At night, soaked in warm water (heat wave is done). Dried feet. Skin feels really dry and itchy, especially outside edges of feet and back of ankles and heels. Barely starting to peel, see thin sliver cracks in dead skin around balls of feet.

        Day 4-6:
        No "big peels," but feet were itchy. Mostly tiny flaking off starting from the soles, the line of flaking working its way up the foot towards the ankle like a water line working its way up.

        (Day 4 I went in a pool for an hour, but only washed and dried feet afterward.)

        Stopped soaking feet for 10 minutes per day after Day 4.

        Post-peeled skin feels naturally hydrated.

        Final 4 pictures are Day 7.
        ----------
        OVERALL IMPRESSIONS
        PROS: Product mostly delivers. The heels of my feet have never looked better. (Love!) Day 7 I still have a bit of a "water line" of minor peeling going on. Skin feels soft where dead skin peeled off. No actual pain experienced. A slight tingle during the mask. I have sensitive skin and sensitivity to scents, but this product didn't affect me negatively at all.

        CONS: If it's summer and you don't have air conditioning, be prepared to SWEAT A LOT while wearing the foot mask with socks, and wearing socks for Days 3 through 7 to keep the dead skin from flaking off everywhere you go. Not the best timing, I'd recommend another season if you don't have air conditioning. Be prepared for the flaking between your toes to be uncomfortable. I have a thick callous under my right big toe, and also 2 small long thin callouses lining the ball of each foot. One round with the mask did NOT remove them. Instructions say for thick callouses to do a "patch" on those spots on Day 2. I did not do this because I wanted to see how well 1 round of the foot mask did on its own. Day 7 I still have a small "water line" of flaking on the space where top of foot meets sole of the foot. Unsure of when that will finally stop and entire foot looks consistent. However, it's minor and not noticeable if you aren't looking for it.

        TIPS: Wear socks at least crew length when doing the mask itself. Days afterwards, ankle socks are enough. Be prepared for slight discomfort of (minor) itchiness. I don't know if results would be different if you moisturize with lotion every day. Be prepared to vacuum a LOT.

      Important Information

      Safety Information

      Do not use this product if you are a pregnant or nursing mother; If you are diabetic (consult your physician); If you are allergic to any of the ingredients in this product (see bottom of package), if you have open sores on your feet or other foot damage, or if you are using any other foot products. Before use, read the directions and follow them carefully. The product should be used immediately after opening plastic booties. Each Sunatoria Foot Mask is a single-use application. Do not re-use plastic booties. Sunatoria recommends staying seated during treatment for your safety. Keep the gel away from your eyes. If you experience any itching, redness, swelling, irritation, or inflammation, wash your feet and see a doctor. If the skin on your feet becomes too dry after using the product, a small amount of moisturizer can be applied. Do not forcibly remove the dead skin from your feet. Let the skin peel naturally. Storage: Keep out of reach of children at all times. Do not expose the product to extremely high or low temperatures and avoid exposure to direct sunlight. Do not use this product after the expiration date.
